reviews.text:
Aloha: this place was one of my favorite pizza places back in the day.  First time back in many years and the place still good. I did not try the pizza on this visit (which was my fav ) but tried their amazing sandwiches.   Hottie Salami is so damn good.   I would only say the bread a bit thick but very soft .  The large was a lot for me, next time having a medium.
This spot is worth it, and they have validated parking.
We had their pizza and it was good. Waited a little bit for it but there was a sign up that said 25-30 minute wait. Only downside is that you had to pay for parking $3.00

Locally-owned pizza place within walking distance of the airport or the bus stop.  Thick pan crust.  Sweet-tasting tomato sauce.  They have great toppings including a smoked sausage topping and a sweet kalua pork topping.  Quick and friendly service.  Dining room feels cramped and merely functional.  Overall, the best meal I had during my 5 days in Hawaii.

I asked the girl behind the counter if she recommended the special sumo  pizza or the special Sumo pipeline sandwich. She said the Sumo pipeline sandwich is really good. I went for it , and let me tell you!...folks do not miss this one. Wow! I can't do this review justice. Da Bomb!!!

5/18/2025 I ordered a pepperoni pizza online and paid/tipped. Arrived just at the time when it was ready, and it was delicious.
I would recommend allowing 30 minutes for them to prepare the pizza as it is busy and often takes that long. Will return again.

editorial_summary.overview: Casual spot with island flair offering creative pizzas, hearty sandwiches & desserts.
